reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Yellow and Lime Green are great for coloring on a white board--not writing
reviews.reviewText: These markers come in great colors! Of course the yellow and lime green color are not good for writing on a white board because they either blend or are too light to see. I feel like these are a waste to include in the set UNLESS you are using it to color or draw a box around text you want to make stand out on a whiteboard. They write nicely and are of good quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great cost alternative to other dry erase markers
reviews.reviewText: I go through a lot of dry erase markers in my math classes because I have the students working at the boards for most of my classes. I found this brand and thought I'd try it out because the price was so good and some of the reviews answered my questions: do they erase easily, do they last.Having tried a couple of different brands in the past (including the name brand), I found some colors (even the name brand markers), and even some markers, just to be more challenging to erase. It didn't seem to matter about the brand. That was the same for longevity. So I tried these markers. I am 1/3 of the way through the first box and they are doing fine. Just like other brands some of the colors are harder to erase (red for example). However, in general I don't see any difference in performance (erasing and longevity) than other brands I've tried. I am satisfied with the purchase and have just made another purchase of them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars more than you need if you don't have a classful of kids
reviews.reviewText: I liked the cost, and the colors. I use them on my whiteboard at home to identify the different domains and "to do's" in my life. Some dried out pretty quickly. Some were not as easy to erase after being on the whiteboard for a month or two. But overall, I'd recommend them. The variety of colors is very motivating.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I am teacher and love all the variety of colors offered in the pack. They have lasted me little over a year with the ones I have left from the school year previously. They are a good marker.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 5, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Decent. Go for it.
reviews.reviewText: Extremely good value. I'm a teacher and have used many brands of markers. These are great. As you can see in the picture the colors are good. Notice I keep my markers in a vertical position. Doesn't matter what brand I've used, if they are upside down or lay horizontally, the ink dries up or is lighter. So no matter what brand I buy/get (even the popular ones which are insanely overpriced) I keep them in an upright position. The orange was a little light when I opened the box upon arrival (the pen you see in the pic) but after being upright it is just fine and brightened up. Who knows how long they are upside down in shipping. So glad I purchased them. I love all the different colors and you get so many. What a plus. Don't think I'll use the popular brand again. Very happy!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent for kids!
reviews.reviewText: These are great for kids! I homeschool a 4.5yr old and a 2.5yr old and we use these on a big whiteboard every morning. reviews.reviewText: J'ai mis en place un grand tableau blanc dans le couloir pour que les enfants puissent s'exprimer dans dépasser sur la mur svp.Franchement les feutres sont vraiment de bonne facture.En plus de cela il y a donc 12 couleurs différents, ce qui est franchement pas mal du tout.Ce que j'aime :- 12 couleurs différentes, c'est le paradis- lots de 5 feutres de chaque couleur, absolument tip top !!- bouchon spécial anti-roulage, c'est bête mais c'est une super idée- facilement effaçableCe que j'aime moins :- rien pour le momentSuper kit de 60 feutres par lots de 5 x 12 couleurs différentes si mes calculs au tableau sont juste.

reviews.reviewTitle: Gran variedad de colores y gran cantidad de rotuladores. Buena calidad. Capuchones anti-asfixia.
reviews.reviewText: PRESENTACIÓN muy cuidada, en caja de cartón con impresión a todo color, que nos desglosa todos los colores de los rotuladores que se nos incluyen. Dentro, los 60 ROTULADORES (5 por cada uno de los 12 colores incluidos) nos llegan "de pie" en un par de bandejas.LA VARIEDAD DE COLORES es estupenda, incluyendo los habituales negro, azul y rojo, junto con un verde oscuro y marrón menos comunes, a los que se suman unos coloridos rosa, naranja, amarillo, verde claro y cian (azul claro) que son de lo más resultones.Cabe destacar que los CAPUCHONES, no sólo tienen agujeros anti-asfixia, sino que además cuentan con una forma que evita que salgan rodando cuando los dejamos apoyados sobre una superficie plana.Un punto MUY POSITIVO es que son INODOROS, pues la verdad es que no se aprecia ningún olor, al contrario que en otros rotuladores similares que he utilizado que, normalmente, tienen un olor como raro que a mí me suele resultar muy poco agradable.En cuanto a SU TINTA, cubre bien la superficie, y realiza trazos muy nítidos. También me ha parecido que resultan fáciles de borrar, si bien es cierto que no suelo dejar secar mucho tiempo los trazos que realizo.En relación con SU PRECIO DE 33'95€ (0'57€/rotulador) cuando lo adquirí, pues veo que actualmente no se encuentra disponible, resulta más económico que otras opciones similares vendidas en Amazon, si bien casi ninguna incluye tantos rotuladores en un único pack.¿Tienes alguna duda sobre este producto? Escribe tu consulta en el apartado de preguntas e intentaré responderte.Y si te ha resultado útil mi valoración o fotos, agradeceré mucho si pinchas el botón 🆄🆃🅸🅻 ⤵️️
